com.ibm.team.process.common.advice
Interface IOperationReport

All Superinterfaces:
org.eclipse.core.runtime.IAdaptable, IProcessReport
public interface IOperationReport
extends IProcessReport

A report which encapsulates the result of advising and possibly executing an operation.

Severity values have the following meaning for an operation report:

  • IProcessReport.OK - no problems have been detected for this operation
  • IProcessReport.WARNING - no problems have been detected for this operation which will prevent the operation from executing, but there is information which the user might want to know about
  • IProcessReport.ERROR - problems have been detected for this operation which will prevent the operation from completing

Operation reports are created automatically by the process framework when an operation is advised.

Clients may not implement this interface.

Since:
0.5

getData

java.lang.String[] getData()
Returns the string data of this report or null if no data has been set.

Operations do not set the data on operation reports manually. Rather, clients set the report data on their advisable operation and the process framework sets this data on the report automatically.

This support is experimental and may be removed at any time.

Returns:
the string data set on this report or null
